The paper deals with computer vision techniques for tracking objects in image stacks, specifically in the domain of connectomics. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel technique for clustering and classification, which could be of interest to researchers in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, which could place it in the sub-categories of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) or software engineering (cs.SD).
